<li><b>STRONGLY ENDORSE</b>  Having voted for many of the ArbCom members I have to assume this is a good-faith act.  But I have to say: this is the worst idea in the history of Wikipedia.  ArbCom is created with a very narrow brief, and that is as it should be.  it is not a governing body.  The simple fact is: the Advisory Council on Project Development has no status at Wikipedia.  Any one of us can invite ten or fifteen people to form Advisory Council No. 2 (or No. 3 or No.4 etc.) on Project Development and it would have <i>the same standing</i>.  ArbCom is not a governing body and has no standing to delegate anything. <a href="" title="User:Slrubenstein">Slrubenstein</a>   |  <a href="" title="User talk:Slrubenstein">Talk</a> 20:10, 17 July 2009 (UTC)</li>
