<li>Add me to the list of people disenchanted with Wikipedia governance.  Like many others, I am in favour of a non-consensus based construct as a leadership entity, but I disagree with the process in constructing the Advisory Council as part of this entity -- and specifically with the decision made by the current ArbCom to delegate themselves as a governing body of sorts.  That being said, I would be in favour of the current &#34;Council&#34; membership staying as an <i>ad hoc</i> group for the purposes of brainstorming a different model of governance (as they appear to be a particularly dedicated group with a broad range of interests on Wikipedia), with the understanding that they are reporting to the community and not to ArbCom -- <a href="" title="User:Samir">Samir</a> 06:09, 20 July 2009 (UTC)</li>
