<dd><b>Addendum</b> The biggest problem, in my view is the growing opaqueness of the markup language. Newbies can&#39;t even figure you how to make a proper ref before their hard work gets deleted by a handful of overzealous deletionists. If you&#39;re worried about usership--as I am--this Committee proposal is not the solution. Making Wikipedia <i>more</i> open and <i>less</i> centralized is. <a href="" title="User:Aelffin">Nathan McKnight -- Aelffin</a> (<a href="" title="User talk:Aelffin">talk</a>) 00:03, 7 August 2009 (UTC) </dd></dl></dd></dl></li>
