<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Statement_by_Jennavecia">Statement by Jennavecia</span></h2>
<p>This project is nothing if not broken, and there&#39;s no improvement in sight. This seems like a good opportunity for focused discussion by established editors with different focuses and experiences on the project. The possibility to see some viable proposals for change to then present to the community seems like something worth going for. What&#39;s the worst that can happen? Great ideas get presented to the community and shot-down in no consensus? Well, that&#39;s the best we can achieve right now, so we might as well hope for the best and see how it goes. <a href="" title="User:Jennavecia">&#60;span style=&#34;font-family:Lucida Handwriting;color:#9B30FF&#34;&#62;<b>ل</b>enna&#60;/span&#62;</a><a href="" title="User talk:Jennavecia">&#60;span style=&#34;font-family:Lucida Handwriting;color:#63B8FF&#34;&#62;vecia&#60;/span&#62;</a> 19:00, 11 July 2009 (UTC)</p>
