<dd>To WTWAG - do you <i>really</i> think that a different group is going to come up with a radically different view of what areas are troubled areas on wikipedia? if not, can you see the benefit of watchnig and advising, until such time as it becomes more community-led/chosen? <a href="" title="User:Casliber">Casliber</a> (<a href="" title="User talk:Casliber">talk</a> <b>·</b> <a href="" title="Special:Contributions/Casliber">contribs</a>) 03:32, 13 July 2009 (UTC)
